{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:wisdom.6",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "wisdom",
    "chapterNumber": 6,
    "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6",
    "summary": "Source text for Wisdom of Solomon 6 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:1",
      "text": "Hear therefore, O ye kings, and understand; learn, ye that be judges of the ends of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:2",
      "text": "Give ear, ye that rule the people, and glory in the multitude of nations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:3",
      "text": "For power is given you of the Lord, and sovereignty from the Highest, who shall try your works, and search out your counsels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:4",
      "text": "Because, being ministers of his kingdom, ye have not judged aright, nor kept the law, nor walked after the counsel of God;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:5",
      "text": "horribly and speedily shall he come upon you: for a sharp judgment shall be to them that be in high places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:6",
      "text": "For mercy will soon pardon the meanest: but mighty men shall be mightily tormented.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:7",
      "text": "For he which is Lord over all shall fear no man's person, neither shall he stand in awe of any man's greatness: for he hath made the small and great, and careth for all alike.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:8",
      "text": "But a sore trial shall come upon the mighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:9",
      "text": "Unto you therefore, O kings, do I speak, that ye may learn wisdom, and not fall away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:10",
      "text": "For they that keep holiness holily shall be judged holy: and they that have learned such things shall find what to answer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:11",
      "text": "Wherefore set your affection upon my words; desire them, and ye shall be instructed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:12",
      "text": "Wisdom is glorious, and never fadeth away: yea, she is easily seen of them that love her, and found of such as seek her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:13",
      "text": "She preventeth them that desire her, in making herself first known unto them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:14",
      "text": "Whoso seeketh her early shall have no great travail: for he shall find her sitting at his doors.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:15",
      "text": "To think therefore upon her is the perfection of wisdom: and whoso watcheth for her shall quickly be without care.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:16",
      "text": "For she goeth about seeking such as are worthy of her, sheweth herself favourably unto them in the ways, and meeteth them in every thought.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:17",
      "text": "For the very true beginning of her is the desire of discipline; and the care of discipline is love;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:18",
      "text": "and love is the keeping of her laws; and the giving heed unto her laws is the assurance of incorruption;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:19",
      "text": "and incorruption maketh us near unto God:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:20",
      "text": "therefore the desire of wisdom bringeth to a kingdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:21",
      "text": "If your delight be then in thrones and sceptres, O ye kings of the people, honour wisdom, that ye may reign for evermore.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:22",
      "text": "As for wisdom, what she is, and how she came up, I will tell you, and will not hide mysteries from you: but will seek her out from the beginning of her nativity, and bring the knowledge of her into light, and will not pass over the truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:23",
      "text": "Neither will I go with consuming envy; for such a man shall have no fellowship with wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:24",
      "text": "But the multitude of the wise is the welfare of the world: and a wise king is the upholding of the people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:wisdom.6.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "wisdom",
      "chapterNumber": 6,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Wisdom of Solomon 6:25",
      "text": "Receive therefore instruction through my words, and it shall do you good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
